r professional development or start a regional alumni chapter*? Look no further and sign up today. Join our alumni network Join our official LinkedIn group Get involved Learn more about the numerous ways to stay in touch with former fellow students and how to enrich your personal network with the knowledge and expertise of our alumni community. You would like to get involved? Whether you are interested in donating your time, talents or resources: We will show you how you can have a lasting impact on the University of Tübingen. Stay in touch Events Get inspired, learn from experts, and gain fresh perspectives on the most pressing topics of our time in our virtual alumni talks. Are you interested in exploring cutting-edge research and learning more about the latest scientific discoveries at the University of Tübingen? Take part in lectures, online and face-to-face, and learn more about current research at your alma mater. Why not plan a trip to Tübingen and participate in a guided alumni tour? Check out upcoming events Research alumni Whether you wish to return to the University of Tübingen or to organize an alumni chapter in your country of residence, our Alumni Relations team will be happy to support you. Learn more about formats specifically designed for our research alumni, our research ambassadors across the globe and about ways to stay in touch with our alumni community. Information for research alumni Alumni stories Supporting and empowering women - that fascinates me! "Over the three months, I built close and intense relationships with the crew members and the refugee women. It was a shared journey of empowerment in which we strengthened each other, regardless of our cultural backgrounds. My farewell was also very emotional. At that moment, I really realized once again how important it is that there are people who are committed to the work of ROSA e.V. and the refugee women." In the interview, Anna Gärtner, who has a degree in midwifery and women's health, talks about her career as a midwife and her commitment to ROSA e.V. - Rolling Safespace for refugee women in Greece. Read the article Read more alumni stories Our mission The alumni network is international, interdisciplinary – and constantly growing. The strength of our University of Tübingen is constituted by its people: our alumni, researchers, lecturers, members of staff, friends and supporters from politics and the economy. We are all connected by a shared pride in the University of Tübingen and a deep respect for its tradition and excellence. The Alumni Relations team is here to keep you up to date on the latest news from the University and to show you how you can support your alma mater. Whether you are interested in donating your time, talents or resources: We will show you how you can have a lasting impact on the University of Tübingen. The University of Tübingen: An excellent research institution and a place for meaningful connections and valuable experiences. Contact us Do you have queries or feedback regarding the alumni network? Please contact alumni spam prevention @uni-tuebingen.de Official LinkedIn alumni group Instagram Your Alumni Relations team Dr. Rebecca Hahn, Inga van Gessel, Sandra Zepernick Celebrate Pride Month 2024 With Us! June is Pride Month! The goal is to celebrate the history, culture, and importance of the LGBTQIA+ community at the university and in the city, to address discrimination, provide education, and promote solidarity. We would like to offer a rich program at our university, so I warmly invite you to contribute to Pride Month 2024 by organizing such things as: • Lectures • (Guest) talks • Panel discussions • Film screenings • Networking meetings • Workshops • Exhibitions • Information booths Find out more https://uni-tuebingen.de/en/universitaet/campusleben/veranstaltungen/zentrale-veranstaltungen/pride-month-2024/ Key services Official bulletins Disabled access Advice for international students Media Semester Dates Jobs Organiz