ice Events FAQ Contact Campaign DAAD Meta navigation Deutsch Easy Read Follow us on #RiverNeckar #BeautifulOldTown #HölderlinTower Tübingen YOUNG, COLOURFUL AND DELIGHTFULLY PICTURESQUE Tübingen half-timbered houses © Vonderweiden/DAAD Open fig caption Tübingen is one of the most beautiful student towns in southern Germany. The pretty Altstadt, the river Neckar and opportunities for trips and excursions in the surrounding area make it an attractive place to live and study. The town is defined by the many students and institutions of the renowned university clinic. Living in Germany Discover university cities Tübingen Close menu Main menu Why Germany Plan your Studies Living in Germany Meet the Community Get in touch Main menu 4 Steps to Germany Types of stay University entrance qualification Aptitude test Prep & Foundation courses German language skills Visa Proof of financing Health insurance Get to know the higher education system Find a course of study Funding Application German course Matriculation Finding accommodation Studying with a child Study opportunities for refugees Studying with a disability Discovering Germany Discover university cities Municipal registration and residence permit Bank account Studies Part-time job Money Health Safety Telephone, internet and post Public transportation Paths after university Career service Application tips On-site advice Events FAQ Contact Campaign DAAD Meta navigation Deutsch Easy Read Follow us on Close menu Filter People from over 140 nations live in Tübingen. For the people of Tübingen, tolerance is a matter of great importance. The town also has an environment-friendly image and most people here are nature lovers. You’ll notice this as soon as you arrive at the station: there are bicycles everywhere. The town wants to avoid too much traffic and polluted air. Tübingen’s Christmas market is also rather special. In the winter, there’s an open-air cinema where local residents and students traditionally watch the cult German film „Feuerzangenbowle“ together. It’s also traditional to drink a mug of „Feuerzangenbowle“, rum punch, which the film is named after. Winter wouldn’t be winter in Germany without a „Feuerzangenbowle“! Cafés, restaurants, shops and student bars abound in Tübingen. You can party at lots of bars in Tübingen, especially on a Saturday night. A pub crawl, or „Kneipentour“, is a typical way of spending an evening at the weekend. You can go from bar to bar and enjoy a beer or long drink. A pub crawl usually ends in one of the bars or small dance clubs. Sources ¹ ² Follow us on Meta navigation Contact Netiquette Imprint Privacy Policy Cookies © Copyright DAAD 2024	{cookies,germany,feuerzangenbowle,cookie,berlin,menu,internet,website,christmas,restaurants,tübingen,netiquette,beer,medicine,cafés,clinic,visa,crawl,saturday,altstadt,parties,mug,riverneckar,party,shops,studies,cinema,kneipentour,university,rum,tips,button,hölderlintower,suggestions,winter,towns,refugees,bar,eu,film,bank,scholarship,telephone,weekend,matriculation,advice,accommodation,copyright,clubs,residence,search,education,market,traffic,test,trips,application,types,foundation,houses,funding,faq,disability,policy,courses,privacy,explanations,insurance,page,night,campaign,selection,plan,cities,law,excursions}	2024-07-14 16:17:27.584226	{https://www.study-in-germany.de/en/imprint/,https://www.study-in-germany.de/en/data-privacy-statement/,https://www.study-in-germany.de/en/,https://www.study-in-germany.de/en/why-germany/,https://www.study-in-germany.de/en/community/,https://www.study-in-germany.de/de/deutschland/unistaedte/tuebingen/,https://www.study-in-germany.de/en/easy-read/,https://www.study-in-germany.de/en/search/?s-q=medicine,https://www.study-in-germany.de/en/search/?s-q=scholarship,https://www.study-in-germany.de/en/search/?s-q=berlin,https://www.study-in-germany.de/en/search/?s-q=visa,https://www.study-in-germany.de/en/search/?s-q=university,https://www.study-in-germany.de/en/why-germany/,https