332e0495-32ce-4315-8826-3a50dca11d03	https://cyber-valley.de/news/silo-ai-joins-cyber-valley	Silo AI and Cyber Valley forge partnership to advance multilingual open source AI | Cyber Valley	{About,"The AI Incubator","Start-up Network",Events,News,Research,Partners,"Public engagement",Jobs,"Silo AI and Cyber Valley forge partnership to advance multilingual open source AI","About Silo AI","About Cyber Valley","Press Contact Silo AI","Press Contact Cyber Valley","Related Articles","The Cyber Valley Start-up Network continues to grow","Cyber Valley: World's first ELLIS Institute opens","Excellence meets capital: Deep Tech & Investor Day brings...","Cyber Valley Newsletter",News,Events,Research,Innovation,"Public engagement",About,Jobs,""}	Silo AI and Cyber Valley forge partnership to advance multilingual open source AI | Cyber Valley EN News About The AI Incubator Start-up Network Events News Research Partners Public engagement Jobs All News 21 June 2024 | Helsinki & Tübingen Silo AI and Cyber Valley forge partnership to advance multilingual open source AI Innovative partnership for a new era of multilingual AI Photo: Cyber Valley Europe’s foremost AI entities, Silo AI and Cyber Valley, forge a strategic alliance to enhance AI capabilities. The partnership focuses on multilingual Large Language Models (LLMs) covering all official EU languages and cooperation with Cyber Valley’s industrial and scientific partners. Open source AI models, promoting privacy, security and ethics, set to offer a robust platform to generate economic and societal value. Helsinki & Tübingen, 21.06.2024 – Silo AI, Europe’s largest private AI lab, and Cyber Valley, the largest center for excellence in AI research, have established a strategic partnership. The joint initiative is aimed at strengthening Europe's position in the AI landscape and building an open source foundation for multilingual AI, covering all official European Union languages. Additionally, the partnership will explore cooperation with Cyber Valley’s industrial and scientific partners. “We’re very happy to partner with the leading center for excellence in AI and modern robotics in Europe, with partners from both academia and industry. Silo AI’s existing research co-operation with the professors Frank Hutter and Matthias Bethge at the co-located University of Tuebingen and ELLIS Institute on open LLMs provides a good basis for collaboration among Cyber Valley’s industrial partners Amazon, BMW, IAV, Mercedes-Benz, Porsche, Bosch, and ZF”, says Peter Sarlin, CEO and co-founder of Silo AI. Rebecca C. Reisch, Managing Director of Cyber Valley, adds: "This alliance represents a remarkable turning point, not just for Cyber Valley and Silo AI, but for multilingual AI development. It resonates with our goal to assist in fostering an AI ecosystem that respects cultural and ethical values that we as the Cyber Valley Community stand for. We are excited to explore this and other opportunities with Europe’s leading private AI lab." Together with partners, Silo AI is committed to developing a series of state-of-the-art, open source and transparent foundation models for European languages, starting with all the official ones, and aiming to include other languages of significant economic and cultural value. The partnership will aim to support this objective and enable even tighter cooperation not just between Cyber Valley and Silo AI, but also with other research and industrial partners. Open source models based on these LLMs will serve as platforms to leverage data for generating wider economic and societal benefits while upholding stringent standards of privacy, security, safety, and ethics. About Silo AI Silo AI is Europe’s largest private AI lab on a mission to ensure Europe has a flagship AI company. We’re a trusted AI partner that brings competitive advantage to product R&D. We build AI-driven solutions and products to enable smart devices, autonomous vehicles, industry 4.0, and smart cities. Silo AI provides its customers unique access to world-class AI models and expertise, as well as the SiloGen model-as-a-service platform. As part of SiloGen, Silo AI is currently building market leading open source LLMst to ensure European digital sovereignty and democratize access to LLMs. About Cyber Valley Cyber Valley is Europe’s largest and leading center for excellence in artificial intelligence and modern robotics. Its mission and public mandate are to advocate for the research, development, application, and acceptance of technologies and methods in the field of intelligent systems. Cyber Valley encourages entrepreneurship by uniting scientific excellence with innovation and technology transfer. In addition, Cyber Valley facilitates critical reflection on the ethical and social implications of AI through public engagement. Cyber Valley envisions a future in which the full potential of intelligent systems is leveraged for the greater good of the world. Press Contact Silo AI Heli Thoren heli.thoren@silo.ai +358 (0) 50 572 9377 Press Contact Cyber Valley Rebecca Beiter Rebecca.beiter@cyber-valley.de +49 (0) 160 9448 1797 Related Articles 28.06.2024 The Cyber Valley Start-up Network continues to grow AskUI, Subsequent, NeurCG, EndoSurge, and Ventus Technologies join the Cyber Valley Com... 21.06.2024 Cyber Valley: World's first ELLIS Institute opens Cyber Valley entering the next phase with new partners 20.06.2024 Excellence meets capital: Deep Tech & Investor Day brings... Cyber Valley Days show the technological AI competitiveness of the state, the federal g... Cyber Valley Newsletter We send out an overview of the most important news and events in the Cyber Valley Community. Only available in English. Privacy Policy Register Register www.CleverReach.de Cyber Valley Cyber Valley Heisenbergstr. 3 70569 Stuttgart Max-Planck-Ring 4 72076 Tübingen +49 711 689 1844 contact@cyber-valley.de News Newsletters Events AI Incubator Research People International Max Planck Research 