 and methods in the field of intelligent systems. The Cyber Valley Community is a network of AI researchers, entrepreneurs, investors, and start-ups, alongside partners from academia, industry, and society. Cyber Valley GmbH is owned by the State of Baden-Württemberg and the Max Planck Gesellschaft. It acts as the service provider, central organizer, and host for the Cyber Valley Community. https://www.cyber-valley.de What is the Ellis Institute Tübingen? The Ellis Institute is set to become a world-renowned center for pioneering basic research in the field of artificial intelligence.The Institute aims to attract the world's best machine learning talent, providing them with outstanding conditions to conduct research in a state-of-the-art facility located in Tübingen, Germany. The vision is part of a broader initiative, the European Laboratory for Learning and Intelligent Systems (ELLIS), which aims to build a pan-European institution for machine learning research. https://institute-tue.ellis.eu Jun 11 1 hr 9 min AI Algorithms and their Impact on Society - Celestine Mendler-Dünner // Cyber Valley Podcast #3 Dr Celestine Dünner is a Principal Investigator at the ELLIS Institute Tübingen, co-affiliated with the Max Planck Institute and the Tübingen AI Center. She develops theoretical and practical tools to understand the interaction between algorithmic systems and society. Before spending two years in the US as a postdoc at UC Berkeley, she completed her PhD at ETH Zurich, where she was awarded the ETH medal and the Fritz Kutter prize for the academic as well as the industrial impact of her research. About the Cyber Valley: Cyber Valley is Europe’s largest and leading center for excellence in artificial intelligence and modern robotics. Its mission and public mandate are to advocate for research, development, application, and acceptance of technologies and methods in the field of intelligent systems. The Cyber Valley Community is a network of AI researchers, entrepreneurs, investors, and start-ups, alongside partners from academia, industry, and society. Cyber Valley GmbH is owned by the State of Baden-Württemberg and the Max Planck Gesellschaft. It acts as the service provider, central organizer, and host for the Cyber Valley Community. https://www.cyber-valley.de What is the Ellis Institute Tübingen? The Ellis Institute is set to become a world-renowned center for pioneering basic research in the field of artificial intelligence.The Institute aims to attract the world's best machine learning talent, providing them with outstanding conditions to conduct research in a state-of-the-art facility located in Tübingen, Germany. The vision is part of a broader initiative, the European Laboratory for Learning and Intelligent Systems (ELLIS), which aims to build a pan-European institution for machine learning research. https://institute-tue.ellis.eu May 17 40 min 47 sec The Challenges of Making AI Safe and Efficient - Jonas Geiping // Cyber Valley Podcast #2 Dr. Jonas Geiping is an expert in safety and efficiency of AI. He studied mathematics and received his PhD in computer science, working in Europe and USA. He is a Principal Investigator at the ELLIS Institute Tübingen, working closely with Max Planck Institute for Intelligent Systems and Tübingen AI Center. He is leading the Safety- and Efficiency- aligned Learning group, aiming to improve safety and efficiency of Machine Learning. Apr 26 46 min 1 sec AI Expert: "We are the reason AI is biased" - Antonio Orvieto // CyberValley Podcast #1 Join us on this enlightening episode of the Cyber Valley podcast, featuring the renowned AI expert Antonio Orvieto. Sponsored by the Ellis Institute Tübingen, this discussion delves deep into the world of artificial intelligence, tackling the complex issues surrounding biased algorithms, the promising horizon of AI technology, and its transformative potential in the medical field. Antonio, with his profound expertise, sheds light on the mechanisms be