84037dd5-57aa-47ab-b94f-f594b3d68452	https://www.bundeswahlleiterin.de/en/europawahlen/2024/informationen-waehler/unionsbuerger.html	Union citizens - The Federal Returning Officer	{"Information for Union citizens","Legal basis","No more applications possible!","Am I entitled to vote in Germany?","Legal basis","How can I take part in the election in Germany?","Legal bases","Can I vote in the member state I come from?","Legal basis",Topics,Downloads,Contact,"Postal address"}	Union citizens - The Federal Returning Officer Scroll to content Start Service navigation Deutsch Accessibility Contact Twitter Instagram Press Menu Hide menu Navigation Bundestag election European Parliament election Political parties Services About us European Parliament election 2024 Start European Parliament election 2024 Information for voters Union citizens Information for Union citizens Citizens of other European Union member states (Union citizens) who live in the Federal Republic of Germany can also take part in the elections to the European Parliament, either in the Federal Republic of Germany or in their country of origin. Legal basis Article 22 (2) of the Treaty on the Functioning of the European Union No more applications possible! Union citizens can no longer apply for entry in the voters’ register. The deadline for application ended on 19 May 2024 . Exceptions are made only where it can be proven that the application deadline was missed by the Germans living abroad through no fault of their own (Section 24 (2) no. 1 of the European Electoral Regulations - EuWO). Please note that the right to vote may be exercised only once and only personally. Am I entitled to vote in Germany? Union citizens residing in Germany can take part in European elections in Germany if, on election day, they have reached the age of sixteen years, they have had a domicile or have otherwise been permanently resident for at least three months in the Federal Republic of Germany or in the other member states of the European Union, and are not disqualified from voting in the Federal Republic of Germany or in their member state of origin. Legal basis Section 6 (3) of the European Elections Act (EuWG) Back to top How can I take part in the election in Germany? A Union citizen who wants to go to the polls in Germany has to be on the voters’ register. Registration ex officio Union citizens entitled to vote will ex officio be entered in a voters’ register by the competent municipal authority if they were enrolled in a voters’ register in the Federal Republic of Germany for the European Parliament election of 13 June 1999 or a later European election, provided they are registered with a residents’ registration office on the 42 nd day before the election (= 28 April 2024) and had not departed to a foreign country in the meantime. Like all others entitled to vote, they will receive a voter’s notification from the municipal authority by the 21 st day before the election at the latest. Union citizens who moved abroad and returned to the Federal Republic of Germany have to re-apply for entry in a voters’ register. Registration upon application Union citizens who are not entered ex officio into a voters’ register (see no. 1.) have to submit a formal application to be registered. The application must have been received by the municipality of their place of residence on the 21 st day before election (= 19 May 2024) at the latest. This period cannot be extended. The application has to bear the applicant’s personal handwritten signature; its original must be submitted to the competent municipal authority. The application must not be sent by e-mail or fax. You may download the application form from this webpage as pdf file. It contains an information leaflet with instructions for completing the form. Printed application forms are available in the electoral office of your municipality. Application form: Antrag für Unionsbürgerinnen und Unionsbürger auf Eintragung in das Wählerverzeichnis zur Europawahl Note for users of the Mozilla Firefox browser: The browser contains a known issue in the integrated PDF viewer which causes that the date of birth entered is always displayed as “01011970”. Please download the PDF file and open it in another PDF program. Legal bases Section 4 of the European Elections Act (EuWG) in conjunction with Section 54 (2) of the Federal Elections Act (BWG) Sections 17a, 17b (1) of the European Electoral Regulations (EuWO) Back to top Can I vote in the member state I come from? Union citizens wishing to elect European parliament members from their country of origin should contact the competent agency of that country for more information. The foreign missions of the respective countries of origin provide further information on legal aspects and the relevant procedures. If you are listed ex officio in a voters’ register in Germany (see question “How can I take part in the election in Germany?”, no. 1) but want to exercise your right to vote in the country you come from, you have to file a written request with the competent municipal authority by the 21 st day before the election (= 19 May 2024) at the latest, stating that you do not want to be on their voters' register. As the de-registration will be permanent, you will have to apply to be registered again if you should wish to vote in Germany in any future European election (see question “How can I take part in the election in Germany?”, no. 2). You may download the application form from this webpage as pdf file. It contains an information leaflet with instructions for completing the form. Printed application forms are available also in the electoral office of your municipality. Application form: Antrag für Unionsbürgerinnen und Unionsbürger, nicht im Wählerverzeichnis geführt zu werden Note for users of the Mozilla Firefox browser in the integrated PDF viewer: The browser contains a known issue which causes that the date of birth entered is always displayed as “01011970”. Please download the PDF file and open it in another PDF program. Legal basis Section 17b (2) of the European Electoral Regulations (EuWO) Back to top Topics Overview News Information for voters Electoral system Union citizens Germans abroad Voters’ register and residential move Voter’s notification Postal ballot Accessibility of voting Representative electoral statistics On the Sunday of the election Electoral scrutiny Facts against fake news Rural and urban districts Structural data Political parties and candidates Dates and deadlines Results Elected candidates Publications Legal bases Downloads Application form (only in German) : Antrag für Unionsbürgerinnen und -bürger auf Eintragung in das Wählerverzeichnis zur Europawahl Antrag für Unionsbürgerinnen und Unionsbürger, nicht im Wählerverzeichnis geführt zu werden Note for users of the Mozilla Firefox browser: The browser contains a known issue in the integrated PDF viewer which causes that the date of birth entered is always displayed as “01011970”. Please download the PDF file and open it in another PDF program. Meta navigation Print page Share page Cancel E-Mail X Facebook WhatsApp Back to top Navigation Bundestag election European Parliament election Political parties Services About us Contact Contact form Postal address Die Bundeswahlleiterin Statistisches Bundesamt 65180 Wiesbaden Germany Data protection Imprint © 2024 The Federal Returning Officer	{germany,germans,bundeswahlleiterin,mozilla,firefox,bürger,eintragung,voter,twitter,fax,election,elections,april,june,unionsbürger,browser,webpage,parliament,voters,wiesbaden,unionsbürgerinnen,polls,parties,17b,ballot,sunday,deadlines,17a,menu,candidates,office,download,mail,deadline,european,republic,downloads,statistics,residence,applications,geführt,article,das,news,regulations,nicht,auf,dates,publications,federal,zur,bases,citizens,residents,results,future,application}	2024-07-14 16:21:30.711373	{https://www.bundeswahlleiterin.de/en/bundeswahlleiter.html,https://www.bu